Note:
Comprehensive Test Suite for GC Visualization Module

Tests all functionality of the garbage collector visualization and monitoring system including:
- Real-time heap state visualization with object graphs
- GC cycle analysis with detailed timing and performance metrics
- Multi-format export: JSON, SVG, PNG, HTML, CSV, PDF
- Live performance dashboards with configurable refresh rates
- Memory heat maps and fragmentation analysis
- Object reference graph visualization with cycle detection
- GC root set analysis and reachability tracing
- Integration with developer IDEs and monitoring systems
- Enterprise-grade monitoring with minimal overhead (<2%)
- AI/agent-friendly visualization APIs
- Production-ready robustness and extensibility
:End Note

Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/memory/gc_visualization" as GCVisualization
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/memory/gc_algorithms" as GCAlgorithms
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/utilities/common" as Common

Note: Test Configuration Constants
Let TEST_HEAP_SIZE be 16777216
Let TEST_OBJECT_COUNT be 5000
Let TEST_REFRESH_INTERVAL be 1000
Let TEST_OVERHEAD_LIMIT be 0.02
Let TEST_EXPORT_FORMATS be list containing "json", "svg", "png", "html", "csv", "pdf"

Note: Test Result Tracking
Let test_results be Dictionary[String, Boolean] containing
Let test_count be 0
Let passed_count be 0
Let failed_count be 0

Note: Helper Functions for Testing

Process called "run_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Function returns Boolean:
    Set test_count to test_count plus 1
    
    Try:
        Display message "Running test: " plus test_name
        Let result be test_function()
        
        If result:
            Set passed_count to passed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to true
            Display message "  ✓ PASS: " plus test_name
        Otherwise:
            Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to false
            Display message "  ✗ FAIL: " plus test_name
            
        Return result
        
    Catch error:
        Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
        Set test_results[test_name] to false
        Display message "  ✗ ERROR: " plus test_name plus " - " plus convert_to_string with value as error
        Return false

Process called "assert_equals" that takes actual as Any and expected as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is equal to expected:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected: " plus convert_to_string with value as expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus convert_to_string with value as actual
        Return false

Process called "assert_not_none" that takes value as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If value is not None:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message plus " - value is None"
        Return false

Process called "assert_greater_than" that takes actual as Number and expected as Number and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is greater than expected:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected > " plus convert_to_string with value as expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus convert_to_string with value as actual
        Return false

Process called "assert_less_than" that takes actual as Number and expected as Number and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is less than expected:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected < " plus convert_to_string with value as expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus convert_to_string with value as actual
        Return false

Process called "assert_contains" that takes collection as List[Any] and item as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If collection contains item:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Collection does not contain: " plus convert_to_string with value as item
        Return false

Process called "create_test_gc_algorithm" returns GCAlgorithms.GCAlgorithm:
    Note: Creates a test GC algorithm for visualization testing
    Return GCAlgorithms.create_generational_gc with config as GCAlgorithms.GenerationalGCConfig with:
        heap_size as TEST_HEAP_SIZE
        young_generation_size as 4194304
        old_generation_size as 12582912
        collection_threshold as 0.8
        promotion_threshold as 5
        concurrent_enabled as true
        metadata as dictionary containing
            "test_mode" as true
            "object_count" as TEST_OBJECT_COUNT

Process called "create_test_visualizer_config" returns GCVisualization.VisualizerConfig:
    Note: Creates a test visualizer configuration
    Return GCVisualization.VisualizerConfig with:
        enable_real_time as true
        refresh_interval_ms as TEST_REFRESH_INTERVAL
        max_object_count as TEST_OBJECT_COUNT
        enable_object_graph as true
        enable_heat_maps as true
        enable_performance_tracking as true
        export_formats as TEST_EXPORT_FORMATS
        performance_overhead_limit as TEST_OVERHEAD_LIMIT
        detailed_analysis as true
        metadata as dictionary containing
            "test_configuration" as true

Note: Core Visualization Tests

Process called "test_create_gc_visualizer":
    Note: Tests creation of GC visualizer with proper configuration
    Let config be create_test_visualizer_config
    Let visualizer be GCVisualization.create_gc_visualizer with config as config
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as visualizer and message as "Visualizer should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as visualizer.config.enable_real_time and expected as true and message as "Real-time should be enabled"
    Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as visualizer.config.refresh_interval_ms and expected as TEST_REFRESH_INTERVAL and message as "Refresh interval should match config"
    Let result4 be assert_equals with actual as visualizer.state.is_active and expected as false and message as "Visualizer should start inactive"
    Let result5 be assert_not_none with value as visualizer.export_handlers and message as "Export handlers should be initialized"
    Let result6 be assert_contains with collection as TEST_EXPORT_FORMATS and item as "json" and message as "JSON export should be supported"
    Let result7 be assert_contains with collection as TEST_EXPORT_FORMATS and item as "svg" and message as "SVG export should be supported"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6 and result7

Process called "test_visualize_state":
    Note: Tests comprehensive GC state visualization
    Let gc_algorithm be create_test_gc_algorithm
    Let visualization_data be GCVisualization.visualize_state with gc_state as gc_algorithm
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as visualization_data and message as "Visualization data should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_not_none with value as visualization_data.heap_map and message as "Heap map should be present"
    Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as visualization_data.object_relationships and message as "Object relationships should be present"
    Let result4 be assert_not_none with value as visualization_data.memory_layout and message as "Memory layout should be present"
    Let result5 be assert_not_none with value as visualization_data.generation_statistics and message as "Generation statistics should be present"
    Let result6 be assert_not_none with value as visualization_data.collection_metrics and message as "Collection metrics should be present"
    Let result7 be assert_not_none with value as visualization_data.performance_timeline and message as "Performance timeline should be present"
    Let result8 be assert_not_none with value as visualization_data.fragmentation_map and message as "Fragmentation map should be present"
    Let result9 be assert_not_none with value as visualization_data.root_set_analysis and message as "Root set analysis should be present"
    Let result10 be assert_greater_than with actual as visualization_data.timestamp and expected as 0 and message as "Timestamp should be valid"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6 and result7 and result8 and result9 and result10

Process called "test_heap_visualization":
    Note: Tests detailed heap visualization functionality
    Let gc_algorithm be create_test_gc_algorithm
    Let heap_visualization be GCVisualization.create_heap_visualization with state as gc_algorithm
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as heap_visualization and message as "Heap visualization should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as heap_visualization.total_size and expected as 0 and message as "Total heap size should be positive"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as heap_visualization.used_size and expected as 0 and message as "Used heap size should be positive"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of heap_visualization.objects and expected as 0 and message as "Should have heap objects"
    Let result5 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of heap_visualization.memory_regions and expected as 0 and message as "Should have memory regions"
    Let result6 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of heap_visualization.generation_info and expected as 0 and message as "Should have generation info"
    Let result7 be assert_greater_than with actual as heap_visualization.fragmentation_level and expected as 0.0 and message as "Fragmentation level should be calculated"
    Let result8 be assert_less_than with actual as heap_visualization.fragmentation_level and expected as 1.0 and message as "Fragmentation level should be valid ratio"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6 and result7 and result8

Process called "test_object_graph_visualization":
    Note: Tests object relationship graph creation and cycle detection
    Let gc_algorithm be create_test_gc_algorithm
    Let object_graph be GCVisualization.create_object_graph_visualization with state as gc_algorithm
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as object_graph and message as "Object graph should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of object_graph.nodes and expected as 0 and message as "Should have object nodes"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of object_graph.edges and expected as 0 and message as "Should have object edges"
    Let result4 be assert_not_none with value as object_graph.cycles and message as "Cycles collection should exist"
    Let result5 be assert_not_none with value as object_graph.strongly_connected_components and message as "SCC should be computed"
    Let result6 be assert_not_none with value as object_graph.reachability_matrix and message as "Reachability matrix should exist"
    Let result7 be assert_not_none with value as object_graph.orphaned_objects and message as "Orphaned objects should be identified"
    
    Note: Validate object nodes have proper structure
    If length of object_graph.nodes is greater than 0:
        Let first_node be object_graph.nodes[0]
        Let result8 be assert_not_none with value as first_node.object_id and message as "Node should have object ID"
        Let result9 be assert_not_none with value as first_node.type_name and message as "Node should have type name"
        Let result10 be assert_greater_than with actual as first_node.size and expected as 0 and message as "Node should have positive size"
        Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6 and result7 and result8 and result9 and result10
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6 and result7

Process called "test_cycle_detection":
    Note: Tests cycle detection in object reference graphs
    Let gc_algorithm be create_test_gc_algorithm
    Let object_graph be GCVisualization.create_object_graph_visualization with state as gc_algorithm
    
    Note: Test cycle detection functionality
    Let cycles be object_graph.cycles
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as cycles and message as "Cycles collection should exist"
    
    Note: If cycles are detected, validate their structure
    If length of cycles is greater than 0:
        Let first_cycle be cycles[0]
        Let result2 be assert_not_none with value as first_cycle.cycle_id and message as "Cycle should have ID"
        Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of first_cycle.objects and expected as 1 and message as "Cycle should have multiple objects"
        Let result4 be assert_equals with actual as first_cycle.cycle_length and expected as length of first_cycle.objects and message as "Cycle length should match object count"
        Let result5 be assert_greater_than with actual as first_cycle.cycle_strength and expected as 0.0 and message as "Cycle strength should be positive"
        Let result6 be assert_less_than with actual as first_cycle.cycle_strength and expected as 1.1 and message as "Cycle strength should be reasonable"
        Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6
    
    Return result1

Process called "test_memory_regions_analysis":
    Note: Tests memory region analysis and visualization
    Let gc_algorithm be create_test_gc_algorithm
    Let memory_regions be GCVisualization.visualize_memory_regions with state as gc_algorithm
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as memory_regions and message as "Memory regions should be analyzed"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of memory_regions.regions and expected as 0 and message as "Should have memory regions"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as memory_regions.total_allocated and expected as 0 and message as "Total allocated should be positive"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as memory_regions.fragmentation_ratio and expected as 0.0 and message as "Fragmentation ratio should be calculated"
    Let result5 be assert_greater_than with actual as memory_regions.largest_free_block and expected as 0 and message as "Largest free block should be identified"
    Let result6 be assert_not_none with value as memory_regions.allocation_patterns and message as "Allocation patterns should be analyzed"
    
    Note: Validate individual memory regions
    If length of memory_regions.regions is greater than 0:
        Let first_region be memory_regions.regions[0]
        Let result7 be assert_greater_than with actual as first_region.start_address and expected as 0 and message as "Region should have start address"
        Let result8 be assert_greater_than with actual as first_region.end_address and expected as first_region.start_address and message as "End address should be greater than start"
        Let result9 be assert_greater_than with actual as first_region.size and expected as 0 and message as "Region should have positive size"
        Let result10 be assert_not_none with value as first_region.status and message as "Region should have status"
        Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6 and result7 and result8 and result9 and result10
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6

Process called "test_generation_statistics":
    Note: Tests generational GC statistics visualization
    Let gc_algorithm be create_test_gc_algorithm
    Let generation_data be GCVisualization.visualize_generation_data with state as gc_algorithm
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as generation_data and message as "Generation data should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of generation_data.generations and expected as 0 and message as "Should have generation info"
    Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as generation_data.promotion_rates and message as "Promotion rates should be calculated"
    Let result4 be assert_not_none with value as generation_data.collection_frequencies and message as "Collection frequencies should be tracked"
    Let result5 be assert_not_none with value as generation_data.survival_rates and message as "Survival rates should be computed"
    
    Note: Validate generation information
    If length of generation_data.generations is greater than 0:
        Let first_gen be generation_data.generations[0]
        Let result6 be assert_greater_than with actual as first_gen.size and expected as 0 and message as "Generation should have size"
        Let result7 be assert_greater_than with actual as first_gen.capacity and expected as first_gen.size and message as "Capacity should be greater than size"
        Let result8 be assert_greater_than with actual as first_gen.object_count and expected as 0 and message as "Generation should have objects"
        Let result9 be assert_greater_than with actual as first_gen.utilization and expected as 0.0 and message as "Utilization should be positive"
        Let result10 be assert_less_than with actual as first_gen.utilization and expected as 1.1 and message as "Utilization should be reasonable"
        Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6 and result7 and result8 and result9 and result10
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5

